title: A Bronx Tale
overview: A father becomes worried when a local gangster befriends his son in the Bronx in the 1960s.

title: Victoria
overview: A young Spanish woman who has recently moved to Berlin finds her flirtation with a local guy turn potentially deadly as their night out with his friends reveals a dangerous secret.

title: Hana-bi
overview: Nishi leaves the police in the face of harrowing personal and professional difficulties. Spiraling into depression, he makes questionable decisions.

title: Silver Linings Playbook
overview: After a stint in a mental institution, former teacher Pat Solitano moves back in with his parents and tries to reconcile with his ex-wife. Things get more challenging when Pat meets Tiffany, a mysterious girl with problems of her own.

title: Funny Games
overview: Two violent young men take a mother, father, and son hostage in their vacation cabin and force them to play sadistic "games" with one another for their own amusement.

title: Manbiki kazoku
overview: A family of small-time crooks take in a child they find outside in the cold.

title: The Godfather: Part III
overview: Follows Michael Corleone, now in his 60s, as he seeks to free his family from crime and find a suitable successor to his empire.

title: Bin-jip
overview: A transient young man breaks into empty homes to partake of the vacationing residents' lives for a few days.

title: Taxi Driver
overview: A mentally unstable veteran works as a nighttime taxi driver in New York City, where the perceived decadence and sleaze fuels his urge for violent action by attempting to liberate a presidential campaign worker and an underage prostitute.

title: Dogville
overview: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado community in exchange for labor, but when a search visits the town she finds out that their support has a price.

title: Les quatre cents coups
overview: A young boy, left without attention, delves into a life of petty crime.

title: Dil Bechara
overview: The emotional journey of two hopelessly in love youngsters, a young girl, Kizie, suffering from cancer, and a boy, Manny, whom she meets at a support group.

title: Pulp Fiction
overview: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster and his wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: Blood Simple
overview: The owner of a seedy small-town Texas bar discovers that one of his employees is having an affair with his wife. A chaotic chain of misunderstandings, lies and mischief ensues after he devises a plot to have them murdered.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: The Departed
overview: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

title: Double Indemnity
overview: An insurance representative lets himself be talked by a seductive housewife into a murder/insurance fraud scheme that arouses the suspicion of an insurance investigator.

title: Scarface
overview: In 1980 Miami, a determined Cuban immigrant takes over a drug cartel and succumbs to greed.

title: 12 Angry Men
overview: A jury holdout attempts to prevent a miscarriage of justice by forcing his colleagues to reconsider the evidence.
